# files & directories manipulation

**mkdir <new directoy name>**
**M**a**K**es a new **DIR**ectory with the name specified

**cd <directory name>**
**C**hanges **D**irectory to specified name

**pwd**
**P**rints **W**orking **D**irectory

honorable mentions 
rmdir , cp , poweroff  
[Useful terminal commands](https://milq.github.io/useful-terminal-commands-ubuntu-debian/)

---

# Package Managment  
`sudo apt-get install <insert name here>`

package manger is a powerful software installation utility, named  apt-get,that collect lot of softwares that we can install it to the system from this package manger.


updating reposotries
`sudo apt-get update` 


u had heard about a package x and want to look for it:
`sudo apt-cache search x`

found it , install it :
`sudo apt-get install x`

----

something wrong happened , reinstall:
`sudo apt-get install x --reinstall`

want to remove the x software:
`sudo apt-get remove x`

[Useful link for reference](https://vitux.com/how-to-use-apt-get-package-manager-on-ubuntu-command-line/)


will update all software in the system:
`sudo apt-get upgrade`

---

example: 
first we will update the packagemanger:
`sudo apt-get update` 

then we will install the mplayer:
`sudo apt-get install mplayer`

